text: By comparing the antioxidant activity measured by DPPH radical scavenging and ferric reducing power ( FRAP ) of Zingiber officinale Roscoe and Cuminum cyminum L . oils , El - Ghorab et al . ( 2010 ) [ 79 ] reported almost similar trends in both methods . Cuminum cyminum , mainly constituted by cuminal , γ - terpinene , pinocarveol , , carotol , α - pinene , sabinene , β - terpineol and linalool , presented the best activity .
